{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"OPERATOR ATTESTATION — human adjudication of the 30 contested plan-review findings (2026-07-16).\n\nWHO: the operator (a human), adjudicating live via AskUserQuestion across 6 rounds this session.\nWHAT: all 30 A/B disputes in runs/disputes.jsonl ruled — TALLY 16 TP / 14 FP. Each disputed finding was shown with both raters' calls and a FULL-PLAN context summary (correcting the adjudication harness's 6000-char PLAN_CAP that had starved the LLM raters on long plans and produced several of the 'ambiguous' rows).\n\nMETHOD/PROVENANCE (auditable in runs/disputes.jsonl `human_label` + `human_label_basis`):\n- 23 disputes ruled individually by the operator.\n- 3 near-duplicate archetypes semantically GROUPED (one ruling -> both members, all member text shown): H013+H015 (parent advisory-disposition gate vs children -> FP), H003+H004 (no proving command in ACs, dropped -> TP good-drop), H011+H012 (false code-fact rationale -> TP real).\n- 4 clear nit/spurious/content-free disputes INFERRED from the operator's own prior authoritative rulings and EXPLICITLY CONFIRMED by the operator (Confirm-4 round, no vetoes): H005, H009 (TP good-drop), H016 (FP noise), S003 (TP good-drop).\n\nTwo findings were fact-checked against the code before ruling: S001 (event_append.py has its OWN write-side EVENT_TYPES frozenset, distinct from the reducer's -> the plan's file_impact omission is a real escaped defect -> FP) and H020 (Rater A's 'cited locations absent' rationale was factually wrong; the plan does provision the reviewbot-tickets-pat -- but the operator still ruled FP as a non-improving nit).\n\nFOLD: harnesses/apply_adjudications.py folded the verdicts to final_label/label_source on every corpus row -- 0 pending-human, 379 gold definite labels (245 TP / 134 FP), 20 ambiguous, 1 unlabeled (a failed Rater-A call). This human adjudication (NOT the LLM kappa) is the authoritative validity basis for the corpus, per the operator-approved scope change. Kappa is reported honestly for transparency (overall kappa 0.47 / Gwet's AC1 0.58 / raw agreement 0.77; stratified in runs/README.md)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784231497387927001,"uuid":"bc13fb72-82ba-4550-a5d1-b97672134c1e"}